# OpenClaw Status — environment variables
# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored; never commit real keys.

# OpenRouter API key — required for the LLM assessment pipeline.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# GitHub token — OPTIONAL but recommended.
# When set, GitHub issues are scouted via the direct GitHub API: one query
# returns reactions (👍), comment counts and body text, so the collector can
# rank issues by community impact and flag which ones affect the assessed
# version. When unset, it falls back to Composio (no reaction data).
#
# Least privilege — only public read is needed:
#   • Fine-grained PAT: Repository access = "Public repositories (read-only)",
#     Permissions → Issues: Read-only, Metadata: Read-only. Nothing else.
#   • or a classic token with NO scopes (public read at 5,000 req/hr).
# Create at: GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
